@startuml sequence_crud_operation
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Generic CRUD Operation (Orders Example — L2-067)

actor "Admin" as Admin
participant "OrdersPage\n(Client Component)" as Page
participant "API Route\n/api/orders/[id]" as API
participant "Drizzle ORM\n(db.update)" as ORM
database "orders.orders\n(PostgreSQL)" as DB

== List (initial load) ==
Admin -> Page: Navigate to /admin/orders
Page -> API: GET /api/orders
API -> ORM: db.select().from(orders)
ORM -> DB: SELECT * FROM orders.orders
DB --> ORM: rows[]
ORM --> API: Order[]
API --> Page: JSON response
Page --> Admin: Render data table

== Update (status change) ==
Admin -> Page: Click "Mark as Shipped"\n+ enter tracking number
Page -> API: PUT /api/orders/{id}\n{ status: "shipped", trackingNumber: "..." }
API -> ORM: db.update(orders).set({...})\n.where(eq(orders.id, id))
ORM -> DB: UPDATE orders.orders SET ...
DB --> ORM: updated row
ORM --> API: Order
API --> Page: 200 OK + updated order
Page --> Admin: Table row refreshed\nwith new status badge

@enduml
